  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple aspects:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers\n- Establishing financial intelligence units\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Key Compliance Requirements\n- Customer identification\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Regular reporting\n- Internal control systems\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n- Extradition agreements\n\n7. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Central banks\n- Specialized anti-money laundering units\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
